{"pagelen": 100, "values": [{"links": {"self": {"href": "data/repositories/osrf/cloudsim-legacy/pullrequests/41/comments/264023.json"}, "html": {"href": "#!/osrf/cloudsim-legacy/pull-requests/41/_/diff#comment-264023"}}, "deleted": false, "pullrequest": {"type": "pullrequest", "id": 41, "links": {"self": {"href": "data/repositories/osrf/cloudsim-legacy/pullrequests/41.json"}, "html": {"href": "#!/osrf/cloudsim-legacy/pull-requests/41"}}, "title": "Make stop_sim function to wait for state.log to be complete"}, "content": {"raw": "This is being [done differently](#!/osrf/cloudsim/src/7c9d77a86a89/cloudsimd/launchers/launch_utils/softlayer/bash/router_init.bash?at=tasks_update#cl-274) for SoftLayer; the latest code is on the `tasks_update` branch, yet to be merged.\n\nThe `stop_sim.bash` on the router is sshing to the sim and calling the `stop_sim.bash` there, counting on it to do the right thing.  Assuming taht the AWS configuration also has a `cloudsim/stop_sim.bash` on the sim, then the same approach should work.", "markup": "markdown", "html": "<p>This is being <a data-is-external-link=\"true\" href=\"#!/osrf/cloudsim/src/7c9d77a86a89/cloudsimd/launchers/launch_utils/softlayer/bash/router_init.bash?at=tasks_update#cl-274\" rel=\"nofollow\">done differently</a> for SoftLayer; the latest code is on the <code>tasks_update</code> branch, yet to be merged.</p>\n<p>The <code>stop_sim.bash</code> on the router is sshing to the sim and calling the <code>stop_sim.bash</code> there, counting on it to do the right thing.  Assuming taht the AWS configuration also has a <code>cloudsim/stop_sim.bash</code> on the sim, then the same approach should work.</p>", "type": "rendered"}, "created_on": "2013-05-21T21:10:27.325152+00:00", "user": {"display_name": "Brian Gerkey", "uuid": "{3d8b5763-9dad-4be7-85c2-a7ab6cd49173}", "links": {"self": {"href": "https://api.bitbucket.org/2.0/users/%7B3d8b5763-9dad-4be7-85c2-a7ab6cd49173%7D"}, "html": {"href": "https://bitbucket.org/%7B3d8b5763-9